A diagonal of a polyhedron is a line segment connecting two non-adjacent vertices. How many diagonals does a triangular prism have? [asy]
import three;
size(100);
defaultpen(linewidth(0.7));
currentprojection = orthographic(-0.2,-1,2/3);

void drawTriangle (real h)
{

path3 y;

y=(0,0,h)--(3,0,h)--(0,3,h)--cycle;

draw(surface(y),white,nolight);

draw(y);
}

void drawRectangle(triple a, triple b, real h)
{

path3 y;

y=a--b--b+(0,0,h)--a+(0,0,h)--cycle;

draw(surface(y),white,black,nolight);
}

drawRectangle((0,0,0),(0,3,0),4);
drawRectangle((0,0,0),(3,0,0),4);
drawTriangle(4);

[/asy]

A diagonal of a polyhedron is a line segment connecting two non-adjacent vertices. How many diagonals does a hexagonal prism have? [asy]
import three;
